The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Brussels, March 21: World Bank president Robert Zoellick today warned of the consequences of a steep decline in economic growth across the world this year. He proposed that the G-20 economies, whose leaders are due to meet in London next month, establish a review process to see whether further stimulus measures would be needed to kickstart recovery.                            
	 New Delhi, March 21: The RBI will buy dated government securities of Rs 10,000 crore through auction-based open market operations on March 25. It plans to add liquidity into the system, cut down the cost for government borrowing and ensure flow of money into the credit market.                            
	 Chennai, March 21: Essar Steel today inaugurated its Rs 75-crore steel processing facility at Oragadam near Chennai. The facility would offer customised steel products.                             
	 Mumbai, March 21: BSNL and RIM have launched the BlackBerry solution for enterprise and individual customers with the BlackBerry Bold, BlackBerry Curve 8310 and BlackBerry 8700g smartphones.                                                                                                                           
